He stresses the importance of checking for bats on the property, since it is possible that accidental destruction of one mother's litter could kill up to 400 females and young people, likely leading to the extinction of the entire local population.
Bats are protected animals and are prohibited by law from killing, harassing, harassing, or destroying their nests.
Elisabeth Ferrell, an official with the Scottish Bat Conservation Trust, urged the public to get involved and help.
